# Coding style conventions

- Prefer functional coding style.
- Use map, find, filter, reduce, some, every, concat, slice, splice instead of for loops
- Use native functions of arrays, Map and Set where they exist
- Use es-toolkit functions where no native function exists
- Use optional chaining and nullish coalescing where appropriate
- Use template literals for string concatenation
- Use arrow functions for callbacks
- Use arrow functions instead of function() {...} style
- Use destructuring for object and array properties
- Use spread operator for array and object concatenation
- Use rest parameters for function arguments
- Use default parameters for function arguments
- Use type annotations for function arguments and return values
- Use type assertions for type conversion
- Use type guards for type checking
